Consider the objective function 

F(X, Y) = sum (i,j) in X a[i][j] + sum (i,j) in Y a[i][j]

When we have a "bad" person, we can switch it to the other side to make them good. 

Notice this necessarily increases the objective function by at least 1!!

If there are no "bad" people, we are done, and this must happen because this function F(X, Y) is bounded above by 50n^2 <= 50^3. Hence brute force switching until objective is reached.
